Q  The answer must be a positive effect that jogging has on one's self esteem. Sweating is a physical effect of jogging, not a psychological effect. Ocean is not related to jogging. Arthritis is a health condition that jogging can help, but not a direct effect on self esteem. Feeling better and feeling pride are both positive effects that jogging can have on one's self esteem. So the answer is feel better (a).

